race.comment: SECURITY ADVISOR (4) boasts a good record over this track and trip, though he did disappoint here two back when in the market. He was better last start at Gatton and showed good early speed from a sticky gate there. Can do the same today, dictate from the front and be too strong. BRAVE BOY (1) has been getting well back in recent efforts, though his run here three back was very impressive over this trip. Again, he's likely to get back from the barrier, but if things go his way in the run he'll be finishing with a wet sail. GREEN MEADOWS (5) is better than we saw last time out and can be in the finish. BATTLESPACE (13) won't be far away.
